cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.HC 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for camera calibration, specifically using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves human perception studies, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of deep learning models suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves geometric reasoning and manipulation of 3D objects, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics).
